<main class="main-content main-content--dashboard">
  <div class="c-toolbar">
    <div class="c-toolbar__row items-center w-full gap-3">
      <%= link_to "Back to batches", admin_grade_import_batches_path, class: tailwind_button_classes(:secondary) %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="c-container c-container--wide c-page">
    <section class="u-stack u-stack--lg">
      <header class="c-card p-8 md:p-10 overflow-hidden relative">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-slate-900 via-slate-800 to-slate-700"></div>
        <div class="absolute -right-16 -top-16 h-56 w-56 rounded-full bg-cyan-400/20 blur-2xl"></div>
        <div class="absolute -left-10 -bottom-20 h-56 w-56 rounded-full bg-amber-300/20 blur-2xl"></div>

        <div class="relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan-200">Faculty imports</p>
          <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-white md:text-4xl">New Grade Import Batch</h1>
          <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-sm text-slate-100 md:text-base">
            Upload faculty gradebooks, run a preview first, and then commit with confidence.
            Advisor feedback remains untouched and grade-derived ratings stay isolated as a separate source.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-white/30 bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-white">Preview-first workflow</span>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-white/30 bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-white">CSV + Excel support</span>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-white/30 bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-white">Duplicate protection</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="grid gap-6 xl:grid-cols-[2fr_1fr]">
        <section class="c-card p-6 md:p-8 u-stack u-stack--lg">
          <div>
            <h2 class="c-section-title c-heading-inline">Upload workbook</h2>
            <p class="c-page-subtitle">Start with a preview to review matches, pending students, duplicates, and derived ratings before making the batch reportable.</p>
          </div>

          <%= form_with url: admin_grade_import_batches_path, method: :post, local: true, multipart: true, class: "u-stack u-stack--lg" do %>
            <div class="u-grid" style="--u-grid-min: 320px">
              <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/70 p-4">
                <div class="c-field">
                  <%= label_tag "files[]", "Import files", class: "c-label" %>
                  <%= file_field_tag "files[]", multiple: true, accept: ".xlsx,.xlsm,.csv", class: "c-input" %>
                  <small class="c-help">Use this for one or more Excel or CSV imports.</small>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/70 p-4">
                <div class="c-field">
                  <%= label_tag "folder_files[]", "Folder upload", class: "c-label" %>
                  <%= file_field_tag "folder_files[]", multiple: true, webkitdirectory: true, directory: true, class: "c-input" %>
                  <small class="c-help">Useful when faculty send one workbook per course.</small>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4">
              <label class="c-toggle cursor-pointer">
                <%= check_box_tag :dry_run, "1", true, class: "c-toggle__input" %>
                <span class="c-toggle__track" aria-hidden="true"><span class="c-toggle__thumb"></span></span>
                <span class="space-y-0.5">
                  <span class="c-toggle__label block">Start with a preview</span>
                  <span class="block text-sm text-slate-600">Preview matches, duplicates, failed rows, and derived ratings without using the batch in downstream views.</span>
                </span>
              </label>
            </div>

            <div class="c-form-actions u-actions u-actions--start">
              <%= submit_tag "Run Import", class: tailwind_button_classes(:primary) %>
              <%= link_to "Back to batches", admin_grade_import_batches_path, class: tailwind_button_classes(:secondary) %>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </section>

        <aside class="u-stack u-stack--md xl:sticky xl:top-4 xl:self-start">
          <div class="c-card c-card--tight border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/70 u-stack u-stack--sm">
            <p class="c-section-title c-heading-inline">Import instructions</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">Choose one path for each upload:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700 list-disc">
              <li><strong>Option 1: Canvas direct grade export</strong> with a <code>mapping</code> sheet to convert assignment scores into competency levels.</li>
              <li><strong>Option 2: Canvas competency export</strong> when Canvas already outputs competency result columns directly.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="c-card c-card--tight u-stack u-stack--sm">
            <p class="c-section-title c-heading-inline">Download example files</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Share these with faculty as a formatting reference.</p>
            <div class="u-actions u-actions--start">
              <%= link_to "Example Canvas Grade Export (.xlsx)",
                          "/grade-import-examples/Example%20Canvas%20Grade%20Export.xlsx",
                          class: tailwind_button_classes(:secondary),
                          data: { turbo: false },
                          download: true %>
              <%= link_to "Example Canvas Competency Export (.csv)",
                          "/grade-import-examples/Example%20Canvas%20Competency%20Export.csv",
                          class: tailwind_button_classes(:secondary),
                          data: { turbo: false },
                          download: true %>
            </div>
          </div>

          <details class="c-card c-card--tight c-card--muted u-stack u-stack--sm" open>
            <summary class="cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">View full formatting guide</summary>
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-white p-4 text-xs text-slate-700" data-controller="markdown-render">
              <textarea class="hidden" data-markdown-render-target="source"># Grade Import Guide

Use this guide for batch uploads.

## Option 1: Canvas direct grade export (with mapping)
- Keep the Canvas grade sheet structure unchanged.
- Include Student SIS ID or Student ID, assignment columns, and the points-possible row.
- Add a sheet named exactly `mapping`.

### Required mapping columns
- `assignment_match_type`: `exact`, `contains`, or `regex`
- `assignment_match_value`: assignment name or keyword pattern
- `course_code`: format `ABCD-000-000`
- `competency_title`: must match approved competency titles exactly
- `score_basis`: `points` or `percent`
- `min_score`, `max_score`, `competency_level`
- `active`: `TRUE` or `FALSE`
- `notes`: optional

Example grouping: for multiple SQL quizzes, use `assignment_match_type=contains` and `assignment_match_value=SQL`.

## Option 2: Canvas competency export (direct)
- Use this when Canvas competency mapping is already configured.
- Keep Student SIS ID or Student ID columns.
- Keep EMHA and RMHA competency `result` columns.
- HPMC columns are ignored.
- A mapping sheet is not required.
- Course code can be derived from file/sheet names, for example `PHPM_633_700` becomes `PHPM-633-700`.

## Approved competency titles (exact match)
- Public and Population Health Assessment
- Delivery, Organization, and Financing of Health Services and Health Systems
- Policy Analysis
- Legal and Ethical Bases for Health Services and Health Systems
- Ethics, Accountability, and Self-Assessment
- Organizational Dynamics
- Problem Solving, Decision Making, and Critical Thinking
- Team Building and Collaboration
- Strategic Planning
- Business Planning
- Communication
- Financial Management
- Performance Improvement
- Project Management
- Systems Thinking
- Data Analysis and Information Management
- Quantitative Methods for Health Services Delivery

## Recommended upload workflow
1. Run as Preview first.
2. Review matches, pending rows, duplicate suppression, and derived ratings.
3. Re-upload to commit after validation.</textarea>
              <div class="guidance-text" data-markdown-render-target="output"></div>
            </div>
          </details>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</main>
